.TH OIT 1 "January 2026" "oit" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
oit \- process and log management TUI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B oit
[\fB\-c\fR \fIconfig\fR]
[\fB\-f\fR \fIprocfile\fR]
[\fB\-\-init\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-update\fR]
[\fB\-\-update\fR]
[\fIprocess\fR ...]
.br
.B oit
\fIcommand\fR [\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Overitall (oit)
is a terminal user interface (TUI) for process and log management, combining
process management (like overmind) with log viewing (like lnav).
.PP
It reads a Procfile to start and manage processes, tracks their output and
optional log files, and provides an interactive TUI for viewing interleaved
logs with filtering, search, and batch navigation.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-config " " \fIpath\fR
Path to config file. Defaults to \fB.overitall.toml\fR.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-file " " \fIpath\fR
Path to Procfile. Overrides the config file setting.
.TP
.B \-\-init
Initialize a new \fB.overitall.toml\fR config file from an existing Procfile.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-update
Skip auto-update check on startup.
.TP
.B \-\-update
Check for updates and exit (doesn't start processes).
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version information.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help information.
.TP
.I process ...
Optional process names to start. If specified, only these processes will
auto-start; others remain stopped but visible. Overrides the
\fBstart_processes\fR config option. Use \fB:s\fR command to start stopped
processes later.
.SH QUICK START
.IP 1. 3
Create a Procfile with your processes:
.RS
.nf
web: bundle exec rails server
worker: bundle exec sidekiq
.fi
.RE
.IP 2. 3
Generate a configuration file:
.RS
.nf
oit --init
.fi
.RE
.IP 3. 3
Edit \fB.overitall.toml\fR to configure log files (optional).
.IP 4. 3
Run \fBoit\fR to start the TUI.
