.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file (\fB.overitall.toml\fR) uses TOML format:
.PP
.nf
# Path to your Procfile
procfile = "Procfile"

# Process-specific configuration
[processes.web]
log_file = "log/web.log"

[processes.worker]
log_file = "log/worker.log"

# Filters
[filters]
include = ["INFO", "ERROR"]
exclude = ["DEBUG"]

# Hidden processes
hidden_processes = ["worker"]
.fi
.SS Configuration Options
.TP
.B procfile
Path to your Procfile (required).
.TP
.B processes.<name>.log_file
Path to the log file for a specific process.
.TP
.B processes.<name>.status
Custom status configuration with pattern-based transitions.
.TP
.B log_files
Array of standalone log files to tail.
.TP
.B filters.include
Array of regex patterns to include.
.TP
.B filters.exclude
Array of regex patterns to exclude.
.TP
.B hidden_processes
Array of process names to hide from log viewer.
.TP
.B ignored_processes
Array of process names to skip entirely.
.TP
.B start_processes
Array of process names to auto-start. If empty or omitted, all processes
start automatically. Processes not in this list remain stopped but visible;
use \fB:s\fR to start them manually. CLI arguments override this setting.
.TP
.B max_log_buffer_mb
Maximum memory for log buffer in megabytes (default: 50).
.TP
.B batch_window_ms
Batch grouping window in milliseconds (default: 100).
.TP
.B context_copy_seconds
Time window for contextual copy in seconds (default: 1.0).
.TP
.B disable_auto_update
Set to true to disable auto-update checks.
.TP
.B compact_mode
Set to false to show full log lines by default.
.TP
.B process_coloring
Colorize process names in the log view (default: true).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I .overitall.toml
Default configuration file in the current directory.
.TP
.I Procfile
Default process definition file.
.TP
.I .oit.sock
Unix socket for IPC communication with running TUI.
.SH EXAMPLES
Initialize a new project:
.PP
.RS
.nf
oit --init
.fi
.RE
.PP
Start TUI with custom config:
.PP
.RS
.nf
oit -c my-config.toml
.fi
.RE
.PP
Use a different Procfile:
.PP
.RS
.nf
oit -f Procfile.dev
.fi
.RE
.PP
Start only specific processes:
.PP
.RS
.nf
oit web worker
.fi
.RE
.PP
Check TUI status via IPC:
.PP
.RS
.nf
oit status
.fi
.RE
.PP
Search logs for errors:
.PP
.RS
.nf
oit search "ERROR" --limit 50
.fi
.RE
.PP
Restart a specific process:
.PP
.RS
.nf
oit restart worker
.fi
.RE
